Rhion, <br>
<br>
  If you become bored with EQ just enough to try out another game, but still keep your EQ account active because you've put so much time and effort into your character, how do they lose again? By you having accounts to two different games?    <br>
   To say it's a silly notion that they might perhaps &quot;adjust&quot; content to steer people into trying their other games is a tad naive. I guarantee the marketing types at Sony are not just sitting there HOPING their other games will be a success. It's long been the assumption (correct or not) within the gaming industry that there are only a certain number of people you're going to get to pay a monthly fee to play a game.  EQ has a good majority of that &quot;pool&quot; of people. Those are the FIRST people they're going to &quot;market&quot; their new games to.  The thing you pointed out about there's no guarantee those games are going to be a success is all the more reason for them to steer you to them by making you bored with this one.  <br>
  <br>
